HEADWORD: Dilettanteism
<hw>Dil`et*tan"te*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
quality of being a dilettante; the desultory pursuit of art, science, or
literature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dilettantish</ent>⟦br⟧
